### House Price Prediction – Summary

The housing dataset consisted of 545 records and 13 features related to house characteristics and amenities. After exploring and cleaning the data, categorical variables were converted into numerical form using one-hot encoding. A Linear Regression model was trained and evaluated, achieving an R² score of approximately 0.65, indicating that the model explains around 65% of the variation in house prices. The most influential features were area, bathrooms, air conditioning, parking availability, and number of stories. The analysis showed that larger houses with better amenities generally have higher prices. Based on these findings, real estate businesses should focus strongly on property size and key amenities when estimating market value and pricing properties.
